# Agent cost / model optimization

Match effort to the request. Prefer **Auto**; MAX off for simple Q&A; MAX on for hard multi-file work.

## Soft model nudge (not a gate)

Once per heavy/light phase, if a different model would help:  
`Model tip: switch to <name> for this — or keep Auto/current and reply to continue.`  
Then continue unless the owner stops you. Do not nag every turn.

## Simple requests (Q&A, “where is X”)

Short answer. No Task/explore agents. No broad greps/verify/smoke unless needed. One targeted lookup.

## Task subagent models (cheapest that works)

| Work | Prefer `model` |
|---|---|
| Quick find / narrow grep / shell-git | `composer-2.5-fast` |
| Routine implement | `composer-2.5-fast` or `gpt-5.5-medium` |
| Hard debug / architecture / security | `claude-sonnet-5-thinking-high` |

No Opus/high-thinking for copy tweaks. Owner-named subagent model must be an allowed Task slug.

## Token hygiene

Tools only when the answer needs repo state. Don’t expand scope. Keep replies short. Prefer globs over always-on rules when adding new `.mdc` files.
